ANTHRAX, CATTLE - CANADA (MANITOBA)
**************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon 18 Aug 2003 8:36 AM
From: Allan Preston <APreston@gov.mb.ca>

Manitoba had its first anthrax case in the Vita area of SE Manitoba --
presumptive positive in our lab on 15 Aug 2003, confirmed in the CFIA lab
in Lethbridge on 22 Aug.
This beef herd has lost 6 or 7 cattle. The herd was vaccinated on the
weekend of 16 Aug 2003, and treated with penicillin at the same time. Carcass
disposal was completed that weekend as well.
This herd is in an area that has had anthrax outbreaks in 2001 and in 2002.
Vaccination in the area was widely practised in 2002, but pretty much
forgotten about in 2003. With the incredible heat wave we have been going
through, the likelihood of more cases occurring is fairly high.
--
Dr. Allan Preston
Director, Veterinary Services Branch
Manitoba Agriculture and Food
